Moving to the forest has been the greatest lesson in surrender and trust. And BOY has that been tested through the past two days! Our little valley was one of the areas hit by storms and freakish floods, leaving us without power or phones/internet from Wed night til just hours ago. My impeccably timed flat tyre meant I was also without a car. 

Our tireless emergency services have worked their butts off to keep everyone safe while Ausnet worked at restoring power. Hugest thanks to them all üôèüèºAnyone else finding themselves kissing light switches this morning? Just me? ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Old Sue would‚Äôve been panicked, anxious and fearful but through the work I‚Äôve been doing, supported by nature, it was so much easier to surrender and trust. Uncomfortable in moments but not anxiety ridden - there‚Äôs a big difference. 

I hope everyone affected is safe and warm and power is returned soon. Good excuse to restock those candles now üòâ
